OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,413,410,140,120,000,100
PN,41213
SC,0013
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F412A1782146887
OL,3,CSir Jeffrey Donaldson guilty of
OL,4,Chistorical sex offences
OL,6,FThe trial next heard evidence from a
OL,7,FPresbyterian minister and his wife who
OL,8,Fhad provided "pastoral support" to
OL,9,FComplainant A and her husband after
OL,10,Fthey had disclosed the allegations of
OL,11,Fabuse.
OL,13,FThe minister told the jury that
OL,14,FJeffrey Donaldson had sent him a
OL,15,Fmessage in 2023 asking for a meeting.
OL,16,FThe man responded, telling the former
OL,17,FMP that it would be "inappropriate" to
OL,18,Fhave the meeting.
OL,26,@pD@NOUpD@_O]yD@UOUyD@cO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}           G13/24
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,413,410,140,120,000,100
PN,41214
SC,0014
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F412A1782146887
OL,3,CSir Jeffrey Donaldson guilty of
OL,4,Chistorical sex offences
OL,6,FThe court heard that Donaldson then
OL,7,Fsent a reply which said: "I just want
OL,8,Fto find a way to say how sorry I am
OL,9,Fand repent before them as I have
OL,10,Fbefore the Lord."
OL,12,FThe jury in the sexual offences trial
OL,13,Fthen heard evidence about a meeting
OL,14,Fbetween Complainant B and Jeffrey
OL,15,FDonaldson at the Christian Family
OL,16,FCentre in Armoy in the 1990s.
OL,18,FB had stayed at the centre after
OL,19,Fdeveloping issues with drugs when she
OL,20,Fwas a teenager.
OL,26,@oD@ZOUrD@QO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}           G14/24
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
